.fire_player_missiles
    LDA player_missiles_unlocked  \ Player-missile launch (called from on_fire_pressed). Gated on `player_missiles_unlocked == 1` (= the player has collected 7 pickups → tier 7) AND `player_missile_step == 0` (= no pair currently in flight). On launch: captures the player position into two parallel slots — upper (player_missile_x[0], player_missile_y[0] = player_x, player_y + 2) and lower (player_missile_x[1], player_missile_y[1] = player_x, player_y - &12). Activates both slots (player_missile_active = {1, 1}), sets sprite-frame = 1 and step counter = 1. Suppresses the upper missile if player_y >= &D8 (too low — would be off-screen) and suppresses the lower if player_y < &A0 (too high). On the next pass, `update_player_missiles` (called per-subframe) drives the pair.
