.plot_player_missile
    LDA #&00  \ Plot one player-missile frame at the screen position already set up by the caller's calc_screen_addr. Selects the sprite via the inline multiply: `LDA #0 / LDX player_missile_frame / loop ADC #&28 / DEX / BNE / SBC #&28 / STA src_lo / LDA #&44 / STA src_hi` — so frame N (1..5) → src = &4400 + (N-1)*&28 = &4400/&4428/&4450/&4478/&44A0. Always 5×8 px. (Note: the existing GRAPHIX cfg labels gfx_missile_0..4 at &4410..&44B0 are inconsistent with this — the actual frames L1689 reads are 16 bytes lower in memory. Either the GRAPHIX labels are off by one, or this routine has a constant-offset bug producing scrambled-looking trails.)
