\ ----- data &1A55..&1A99 -----
.enemy_x
    \ Enemy slot pool — 11 bytes per array (slots 0..10), but only indices 1..n_enemies (1..8) are ever populated. Active per-slot state: enemy_x[i] / enemy_y[i] = screen position; enemy_state[i] = animation/lifecycle counter (0 = free, 1..8 = active, 9 = expiring, &0A = just hit / about to free). Plus enemy_pattern_step[i] (the byte-offset into the per-pattern motion script pointed at by zp_88) and enemy_pattern_id[i] (pattern selector 1..6, captured at spawn). Spawned by spawn_periodic_enemy with enemy_x = &25; per-frame stepped by update_enemies which calls L1B87 to walk each slot's script.
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA
.enemy_y
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA
.enemy_state
    EQUB &EA, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00
    EQUB &00, &00, &00
.enemy_pattern_step
    \ Enemy per-slot pattern-step counter — byte-offset into the per-pattern motion script that update_enemies/L1B87 is currently walking. The script (pointed at by zp_88, length enemy_pattern_len bytes) is a sequence of (dy_dir, dx_dir) byte pairs. L1B87 reads `(zp_88),Y` at Y = enemy_pattern_step[X] into data_16F6 (vertical-dir) and `(zp_88),Y+1` into data_16F7 (horizontal-dir), then INYs twice; the next frame's L1B2D stashes the new Y back here. Wrap-around at enemy_pattern_len.
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA
.enemy_pattern_id
    \ Enemy per-slot pattern ID — selects which motion pattern the slot follows. Set at spawn by spawn_periodic_enemy (cycles 1..6 via zp_86). Values 5 and 6 are special-cased in L1B87 (player-homing: pattern 5 toggles horizontal dir based on player_x; pattern 6 = straight at the player). Other values walk the table at (zp_88) verbatim. Slot 0 unused, slots 1..n_enemies (1..8) active; only 10 bytes wide (vs 11 for the position/state arrays) because enemy_pattern_id slot 10 wasn't allocated.
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA
.hazard_bullet_x
    EQUB &FF, &FF, &FF, &FF, &FF, &FF, &FF
.hazard_bullet_y
    EQUB &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00

\ ----- code &1A99..&1C0C -----
.enemy_try_fire_bullet
    JSR lfsr_random  \ Enemy 'try to fire a bullet' hook — called from update_enemies after plotting each active enemy slot. Random chance (rndval32 == 2 → 1/16) gates each call; further requires the enemy to be near the left edge (enemy_x < &10), the global cooldown zp_7E to be 0, and a free slot in hazard_bullet_x[4..1]. On success: stores enemy_x+2 / enemy_y-8 into the chosen slot, sets zp_7E = 8 (8-frame cooldown), plays sfx_hit_lo. Shares the hazard_bullet_x/_y pool with enqueue_hazard_bullet — enemies and hazards fire the same bullet sprite.
    LDA rndval32
    CMP #&02
    BEQ L1AA4
    RTS
.L1AA4
    LDA enemy_x,X
    CMP #&10
    BCC L1AAE
    JMP L1AAF
.L1AAE
    RTS
.L1AAF
    LDA zp_7E
    CMP #&00
    BEQ hazard_bullet_alloc
    RTS

.hazard_bullet_alloc
    LDX #n_enemy_bullets
.L1AB8
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X
    CMP #&FF
    BEQ L1AC3
    DEX
    BNE L1AB8
    RTS
.L1AC3
    STX data_16F6
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA enemy_x,X
    CLC
    ADC #&02
    LDX data_16F6
    STA hazard_bullet_x,X
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA enemy_y,X
    SEC
    SBC #&08
    LDX data_16F6
    STA hazard_bullet_y,X
    LDA #&08
    STA zp_7E
    JMP sfx_hit_lo

.update_enemies
    LDX #n_enemies  \ Per-frame enemy update: iterate the 8 enemy slots (X=8..1 in enemy_state), move each by ±1 X / ±4 Y depending on data_16F6/16F7 direction bits, erase + redraw at the new position with a 4x24 sprite. Slot deactivates (and is erased) when enemy_state drops to 0. Enemies damage the player on contact (check_player_collisions) and are destructible by player bullets (check_bullet_hits).
.L1AED
    LDA enemy_state,X
    BNE L1AF8
    DEX
    BNE L1AED
    JMP update_hazard_bullets
.L1AF8
    INC zp_frame_progress
    INC zp_frame_progress
    JSR pod_collide_enemy
    JSR L1C5D
    JSR L1B87
    BNE L1B2D
.L1B07
    LDA #&00
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDY enemy_y,X
    LDA enemy_x,X
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #&7D
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #&80
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&18
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    JMP L1AED
.L1B2D
    TYA
    STA enemy_pattern_step,X
    LDA data_16F6
    BEQ L1B4F
    CMP #&01
    BEQ L1B46
    LDA enemy_y,X
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA enemy_y,X
    JMP L1B4F
.L1B46
    LDA enemy_y,X
    CLC
    ADC #&04
    STA enemy_y,X
.L1B4F
    LDA data_16F7
    BEQ L1B61
    CMP #&01
    BNE L1B5E
    INC enemy_x,X
    JMP L1B61
.L1B5E
    DEC enemy_x,X
.L1B61
    LDA enemy_y,X
    TAY
    LDA enemy_x,X
    BEQ L1B07
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    JSR enemy_anim_dispatch
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&18
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR enemy_try_fire_bullet
    LDX data_16F5
    DEX
    BEQ L1B84
    JMP L1AED
.L1B84
    JMP update_hazard_bullets

.L1B87
    LDA enemy_pattern_id,X
    CMP #&05
    BEQ L1BA5
    CMP #&06
    BEQ L1BD1
    LDY enemy_pattern_step,X
    LDA (zp_88),Y
    STA data_16F6
    INY
    LDA (zp_88),Y
    STA data_16F7
    INY
    CPY enemy_pattern_len
    RTS
.L1BA5
    LDA zp_7F
    CMP #&04
    BNE L1BD1
    LDA #&03
    STA data_16F7
    LDA zp_player_y
    CMP enemy_y,X
    BCC L1BC4
    LDA #&01
    STA data_16F6
    LDY enemy_pattern_step,X
    INY
    CPY enemy_pattern_len
    RTS
.L1BC4
    LDA #&03
    STA data_16F6
    LDY enemy_pattern_step,X
    INY
    CPY enemy_pattern_len
    RTS
.L1BD1
    LDA #&03
    STA data_16F7
    LDA #&00
    STA data_16F6
    LDY enemy_pattern_step,X
    INY
    CPY enemy_pattern_len
    RTS

.enemy_anim_dispatch
    LDX data_16F5  \ Enemy sprite-frame dispatcher (X = data_16F5 = current enemy slot). For enemy_state in 0..6 it indexes into the parallel `enemy_anim_ptr_lo` / `enemy_anim_ptr_hi` LUT: slots 1..4 → `lev_enemy_0..3` (LEVD1), slots 5..6 → `gfx_enemy_small_frame0/1` (GRAPHIX, two 4×24 winged-creature frames). For state >= &0A it dispatches to one of the hit-animation routines, each of which advances the state by 1 and sets sprite_src for the caller's plot: &0A → enemy_hit_frame1 (lev_enemy_hit_1), &0B → enemy_hit_frame2 (lev_enemy_hit_2), &0C → enemy_hit_frame3 (lev_enemy_hit_3), &0D → enemy_hit_erase (sprite_src = lev_erase_brush + &80, and enemy_state = 0 — clears the slot).
    LDA enemy_state,X
    CMP #&0A
    BCC L1BFB
    BEQ enemy_hit_frame1
    CMP #&0B
    BEQ enemy_hit_frame2
    CMP #&0C
    BEQ enemy_hit_frame3
    CMP #&0D
    BEQ enemy_hit_erase
.L1BFB
    TAX
    LDA enemy_anim_ptr_lo,X
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA enemy_anim_ptr_hi,X
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

\ ----- data &1C0C..&1C1A -----
\ Per-state animation-frame sprite-pointer LUT (parallel LSB+HSB tables, 7 entries each, indexed by enemy_state in [0..6]). Read by enemy_anim_dispatch (L1BE3). Slot 0 = &EAEA (placeholder; state 0 = inactive, never plotted). Slots 1..4 = lev_enemy_0..3 (the four 4×24 small-enemy frames in LEVD1). Slots 5..6 = gfx_enemy_small_frame0/1 in GRAPHIX (two 4×24 frames of a winged creature). Earlier GRAPHIX cfg labels mis-split this region into gfx_pad/gfx_bomb/3×24-frames; corrected in Session 22 to two contiguous 4×24 sprites at &4840 and &48A0, exactly back-to-back to the IRQ handler at &4900.
.enemy_anim_ptr_lo
    EQUB &EA
    EQUB LO(lev_enemy_0)
    EQUB LO(lev_enemy_1)
    EQUB LO(lev_enemy_2)
    EQUB LO(lev_enemy_3)
    EQUB LO(gfx_enemy_small_frame0)
    EQUB LO(gfx_enemy_small_frame1)
.enemy_anim_ptr_hi
    EQUB &EA
    EQUB HI(lev_enemy_0)
    EQUB HI(lev_enemy_1)
    EQUB HI(lev_enemy_2)
    EQUB HI(lev_enemy_3)
    EQUB HI(gfx_enemy_small_frame0)
    EQUB HI(gfx_enemy_small_frame1)

\ ----- code &1C1A..&1E46 -----
.enemy_hit_frame1
    TAY  \ Per-frame plot setup for enemy_state &0A → advances state to &0B and points sprite_src at lev_enemy_hit_1 (&4C20). The caller (update_enemy_slot) then performs the actual sprite_plot_xy with the standard 4×24 dimensions. First of three hit-animation frames played when an enemy has just been killed.
    INY
    TYA
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDA #HI(lev_enemy_hit_1)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #LO(lev_enemy_hit_1)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    RTS

.enemy_hit_frame2
    TAY  \ Per-frame plot setup for enemy_state &0B → advances to &0C, sprite_src = lev_enemy_hit_2 (&4C68). Second hit-animation frame.
    INY
    TYA
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDA #HI(lev_enemy_hit_2)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #LO(lev_enemy_hit_2)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    RTS

.enemy_hit_frame3
    TAY  \ Per-frame plot setup for enemy_state &0C → advances to &0D, sprite_src = lev_enemy_hit_3 (&4CB0). Third (final visible) hit-animation frame. Note: the LSB constant `&B0` is written as `LO(lev_enemy_hit_3)` (the byte happens to equal `LO(lev_erase_brush + &B0)` too — the original author may have used the brush form as a typing shortcut; we render the level-data form for clarity).
    INY
    TYA
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDA #HI(lev_enemy_hit_3)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #LO(lev_enemy_hit_3)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    RTS

.enemy_hit_erase
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)  \ Per-frame plot setup for enemy_state &0D → ERASE the enemy: points sprite_src at lev_erase_brush + &80 (the all-zeros erase brush) and clears enemy_state to 0 (releases the slot for re-spawn). The caller plots a 4×24 black rectangle over the last hit-frame position. This is the final step of the enemy-death animation chain &0A → &0B → &0C → &0D.
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #&00
    STA enemy_state,X
    RTS

.L1C5D
    STX data_16F5
    LDA enemy_state,X
    CMP #&0A
    BCC L1C68
    RTS
.L1C68
    LDY enemy_x,X
    INY
    STY zp_test_x
    LDA enemy_y,X
    SEC
    SBC #&0C
    STA zp_test_y
    LDX #&FF
.L1C78
    INX
    CPX #&08
    BNE L1C83
    LDX data_16F5
    JMP L1CB1
.L1C83
    LDA hazard_type,X
    BEQ L1C78
    LDA zp_test_x
    CMP hazard_x,X
    BCC L1C78
    SBC #&06
    CMP hazard_x,X
    BCS L1C78
    LDA zp_test_y
    CMP hazard_y,X
    BCS L1C78
    ADC #&20
    CMP hazard_y,X
    BCC L1C78
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA #&0A
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDA #&07
    JMP OSWRCH
.L1CB1
    LDY player_missile_x
    INY
    INY
    STY zp_test_x
    LDA player_missile_y
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA player_missile_active
    CMP #&01
    BNE L1CCC
    LDY #&00
    JSR L1CE1
.L1CCC
    LDA player_missile_y + 1
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA player_missile_active + 1
    CMP #&01
    BNE L1CE0
    LDY #&01
    JSR L1CE1
.L1CE0
    RTS

.L1CE1
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA enemy_x,X
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L1CEC
    RTS
.L1CEC
    ADC #&05
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS L1CF3
    RTS
.L1CF3
    LDA enemy_y,X
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCS L1CFB
    RTS
.L1CFB
    SBC #&20
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC L1D02
    RTS
.L1D02
    JSR sfx_explode
    TYA
    TAX
    LDA #&00
    STA player_missile_active,X
    LDY player_missile_y,X
    LDX player_missile_x
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&05
    LDY #&08
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA #&0A
    STA enemy_state,X
    JSR add_score_x1
    INC pickup_kill_count
    RTS

.update_hazard_bullets
    LDX #n_hazard_bullets  \ Per-frame mover for the 6-slot hazard_bullet pool. For each active slot (hazard_bullet_x[X] != &FF): DEC X by 2 (move left 2 px), then either deactivate (X underflowed past &00 or new X <= 1) or re-plot the 4×2-px white bullet at the new position via a 3×2 read of `hazard_bullet_sprite` (visible col + 2-col zero trail). Each active slot then runs hazard_bullet_collide_player to test against the player ship and trigger lose_a_life on hit. Also DECs the global enemy-fire cooldown zp_7E.
.L1D37
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X
    CMP #&FF
    BEQ L1D94
    LDY hazard_bullet_y,X
    DEC hazard_bullet_x,X
    DEC hazard_bullet_x,X
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X
    STX data_16F5
    TAX
    CMP #&27
    BCC L1D75
.L1D52
    INX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA #&FF
    STA hazard_bullet_x,X
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&02
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &102)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &102)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    JMP L1D94
.L1D75
    CMP #&00
    BEQ L1D52
    CMP #&01
    BEQ L1D52
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&03
    LDY #&02
    LDA #LO(hazard_bullet_sprite)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(hazard_bullet_sprite)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
.L1D94
    JSR hazard_bullet_collide_player
    DEX
    BNE L1D37
    LDA zp_7E
    BEQ L1DA0
    DEC zp_7E
.L1DA0
    RTS

.hazard_bullet_collide_player
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X  \ Box-collision test for one hazard_bullet against the player. Hit window: player_x in [bullet_x, bullet_x+5] AND player_y in [bullet_y, bullet_y+&10]. On hit: erase the 2×2 bullet trail with lev_erase_brush+&102, mark the slot inactive (&FF), and fall through into lose_a_life.
    STA zp_test_x
    LDA hazard_bullet_y,X
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA zp_player_x
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L1DB2
    RTS
.L1DB2
    LDA zp_player_x
    ADC #&05
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L1DBD
    JMP L1DBE
.L1DBD
    RTS
.L1DBE
    LDA zp_player_y
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC L1DBD
    SBC #&10
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC L1DCB
    RTS
.L1DCB
    LDY hazard_bullet_y,X
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&02
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &102)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &102)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA #&FF
    STA hazard_bullet_x,X

.lose_a_life
    STX data_16F5  \ Per-hit handler — runs once each time the player ship is touched by a enemy / hazard / bullet (see check_player_collisions). Plays OSWRCH 7 (the redefined BBC bell). Toggles lives_blink_state (0↔1) and DECs player_hp on every other call — so player_hp drops by 1 per actual death, with the blink toggle in between giving a two-frame red/yellow flash on the ship icon at the bottom of the screen. The icon is redrawn at column (player_hp + &1F), row &5F, using gfx_icon_03 (state 0) or the alternate icon at &48B8 (state 1). When player_hp hits 0 AND the blink-toggle says state 1, JMP death_anim (= explosion + DEC lives_left + init).
    LDA #&07
    JSR OSWRCH
    LDA lives_blink_state
    EOR #&01
    STA lives_blink_state
    CMP #&00
    BNE L1E05
    DEC player_hp
.L1E05
    LDA player_hp
    ADC #&1F
    LDY #&5F
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #&48
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #LO(gfx_icon_03)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDY lives_blink_state
    CPY #&00
    BNE L1E2B
    LDA #HI(gfx_icon_03)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #&B8
    STA sprite_src_lo
.L1E2B
    LDX #&01
    LDY #&08
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA player_hp
    BEQ L1E3B
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS
.L1E3B
    LDA lives_blink_state
    CMP #&01
    BEQ death_anim
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

\ ----- data &1E46..&1E47 -----
.lives_blink_state
    \ Lives-icon blink-state — 0/1 toggle stepped by lose_a_life. Used both to swap the lives-icon sprite (gfx_icon_03 vs &48B8) and to halve the rate at which player_hp drops (DEC only on alternate calls).
    EQUB &EA

\ ----- code &1E47..&2050 -----
.death_anim
    LDA #&01  \ Player death animation. Plays sfx_explode then plots 6 frames of a 4×32 explosion sprite (`lev_explosion_0..5`) at the player position with `frame_delay` between frames. The source pointer pairs live in slots 21..26 of `lev_hazard_ptr_*` (aliased as `lev_explosion_ptr_lo` / `_hi` at &7A95 / &7AD5). Frames 0..3 are in LEVD1 (`lev_explosion_0..3` at &4A00 / &4A80 / &4B00 / &4B80); frames 4..5 are in LEVD2 (`lev_explosion_4..5` at &7C00 / &7C80). After the last frame, DEC `lives_left` and redraw the lives-remaining indicator at row &57; if any lives are left, also plays intro_get_ready and re-runs init to start the next ship.
    STA zp_sprite_dir_flag
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDA zp_player_y
    CLC
    ADC #&04
    STA zp_player_y
    TAY
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    JSR sfx_explode
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo + 1
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi + 1
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo + 2
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi + 2
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo + 3
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi + 3
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo + 4
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi + 4
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    LDX zp_player_x
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&20
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_lo + 5
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_explosion_ptr_hi + 5
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR frame_delay
    DEC lives_left
    LDA lives_left
    ADC #&1F
    LDY #&57
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&01
    LDY #&08
    LDA #&48
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA #&00
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA lives_left
    BEQ L1F50
    JSR intro_get_ready
.L1F50
    LDX #&20
    LDY #&5F
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX zp_9A
    LDY #&08
    STY sprite_src_lo
    LDA #&48
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR init
    LDA lives_left
    BEQ L1F72
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS
.L1F72
    LDX #&20
    LDY #&57
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&06
    LDY #&08
    STY sprite_src_lo
    LDA #&48
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDY #&00
    RTS

.init
    LDA #&01  \ Per-level init. Sets player start position (&05, &C8), zero-fills the six 9-slot hazard state tables (hazard_x, hazard_y, hazard_type, hazard_hp, hazard_step, enemy_state), clears single-byte state (player bullets, force-pod registers), sets fire_cooldown_reload=6, and marks all 7 hazard_bullet_x slots inactive (&FF).
    STA lives_blink_state
    LDA #&05
    STA zp_player_x
    LDA #&C8
    STA zp_player_y
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_scroll_col
    STA zp_7B
    STA zp_7C
    LDA #&80
    STA zp_tile_upper_lo
    STA zp_tile_lower_lo
    LDA #&7D
    STA zp_tile_lower_hi
    STA zp_tile_upper_hi
    LDA #&00
    STA stage_clear_flag
    LDX #&00
.L1FB6
    LDA #&00
    STA hazard_y,X
    STA hazard_x,X
    STA hazard_type,X
    STA hazard_hp,X
    STA hazard_step,X
    STA enemy_state,X
    INX
    CPX #n_state_slots
    BNE L1FB6
    STA player_missile_active
    STA player_missile_active + 1
    STA pickup_state
    STA player_missile_x
    STA player_bullet_x
    STA data_16E7
    STA data_16E8
    STA data_16E9
    STA enemy_pattern_len
    STA data_16EA
    STA data_16EB
    STA data_16EC
    STA zp_7E
    STA zp_88
    STA zp_get_ready_erase
    LDA #&77
    STA zp_89
    LDA #&0A
    STA zp_87
    LDA #&01
    STA zp_86
    LDA #&06
    STA fire_cooldown_reload
    LDA #&00
    STA pickup_kill_count
    STA pickup_tier_flag
    STA pod_attached
L2016            = * + 1
    STA force_pod_state
    STA player_missiles_unlocked
    STA data_25A9
    STA pickup_count
    LDX data_16F5
    LDY #&00
    LDA #&FF
    STA hazard_bullet_x
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 1
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 2
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 3
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 5
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 6
    STA hazard_bullet_x + 4
    LDA zp_9A
    STA player_hp
    LDA #&00
    STA flame_state
    STA force_pod_x
    LDA #&C8
    STA force_pod_y
    RTS

\ ----- data &2050..&208A -----
.player_hp
    \ Per-life HP — how many lose_a_life calls the current ship can absorb before it explodes. Reset to zp_9A by init (= zp_9A default 6, configurable from options.BAS as `?&9A = X%`). DEC'd in pairs by lose_a_life (every other call); when it hits 0 the next lose_a_life jumps to death_anim. Also used as the X-position of the lives icon in the bottom-status row (col player_hp + &1F).
    EQUB &06
.lives_left
    \ Lives counter — number of ships remaining BEFORE the current one (i.e. continues / extra lives). Initialised by restore_score_from_loader from loader_lives_save (= 3 at game start; preserved across levels). DEC'd by death_anim after the explosion plays. main_loop polls this each game_step: when it reaches 0 → JMP game_over_or_continue.
    EQUB &06
.hazard_x
    EQUB &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00
    EQUB &00, &EA
.hazard_y
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.hazard_type
    EQUB &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00
    EQUB &00
.hazard_flip
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.hazard_hp
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.hazard_step
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA

\ ----- code &208A..&23C5 -----
.spawn_check_step
    LDX zp_7B  \ Spawn-table scanner — runs once per frame from main_loop. Compares lev_spawn_col[zp_7B] against zp_scroll_col; on match, decodes the paired lev_spawn_attr byte into a new hazard in the slot pool: bits 0..4 → hazard_type (0..31), bit 7 → hazard_flip (INVERTED: 0 in attr = upright, 1 = vertical-flip), bits 5..6 → spawn row 0..3 mapped to Y = &DF / &BF / &9F / &7F (4 evenly-spaced lines spanning the playfield gap between the upper and lower tile bands). Initial slot state: hazard_x = &28 (off-screen right, col 40), hazard_hp = &14 for type &10 / &06 for types &07 and < &03 / &08 otherwise, hazard_step = 4. Allocates slot via zp_7C (round-robin 0..7). On any non-spawning type (3..6 special-cased) it re-enters spawn_check_step to drain back-to-back spawns at the same column.
    LDA lev_spawn_col,X
    CMP zp_scroll_col
    BEQ L2094
    RTS
.L2094
    LDA lev_spawn_attr
    BNE L209A
    RTS
.L209A
    INC zp_7C
    LDA zp_7C
    CMP #n_hazards
    BCC L20A6

.tbl_20A2
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_7C
.L20A6
    INC zp_7B
    LDA lev_spawn_attr,X
    TAY
    LDX zp_7C
    AND #&1F
    STA hazard_type,X
    TYA
    AND #&80
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    EOR #&01
    STA hazard_flip,X
    TYA
    AND #&60
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    TAX
    INX
    LDA #&FF
    SEC
.L20CF
    SBC #&20
    DEX
    BNE L20CF
    LDX zp_7C
    STA hazard_y,X
    LDA #&28
    STA hazard_x,X
    LDA #&08
    STA hazard_hp,X
    LDA #&04
    STA hazard_step,X
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&10
    BEQ L20FA
    CMP #&07
    BEQ L2102
    CMP #&03
    BCC L2102
    JMP spawn_check_step
.L20FA
    LDA #&14
    STA hazard_hp,X
    JMP spawn_check_step
.L2102
    LDA #&06
    STA hazard_hp,X
    JMP spawn_check_step

.update_hazards
    LDA forcefield_active  \ Per-frame hazard + force-field update + plot. First clears the force-field strip if forcefield_active=1 (erases a 2×&20 rectangle at (forcefield_x, forcefield_y) and clears the flag — the strip is procedural noise re-drawn every frame, so it has to be wiped before forcefield_render generates a fresh one). Then iterates the 8 hazard slots: for each active hazard (hazard_type != 0), DEC hazard_x to scroll it left, redraw, and dispatch any per-type behaviour via hazard_type_dispatch.
    CMP #&01
    BNE L2130
    LDX forcefield_x
    LDY forcefield_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #&00
    STA forcefield_active
.L2130
    LDA flame_state
    BEQ L2138
    JSR update_flame
.L2138
    LDX #&FF
.L213A
    INX
    LDA hazard_type,X
    BNE L2151
.L2140
    CPX #n_hazards
    BNE L213A
    INC zp_7F
    LDA zp_7F
    CMP #&05
    BNE L2150
    LDA #&03
    STA zp_7F
.L2150
    RTS
.L2151
    INC zp_frame_progress
    INC zp_frame_progress
    STX data_16F5
    JSR update_hazard_slot
    LDA zp_scroll_col
    CMP #&F0
    BEQ L2164
    DEC hazard_x,X
.L2164
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP #&FF
    BNE L216E
    JMP L21F1
.L216E
    LDY hazard_y,X
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_flip,X
    STA zp_sprite_dir_flag
    LDA hazard_type,X
    TAX
    LDA lev_hazard_ptr_lo,X
    CLC
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA lev_hazard_ptr_hi,X
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP #&25
    BCC L21BA
    CMP #&27
    BNE L21A1
    LDX #&01
    JMP L21AC
.L21A1
    CMP #&26
    BNE L21AA
    LDX #&02
    JMP L21AC
.L21AA
    LDX #&03
.L21AC
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    JSR missile_collide_hazard
    JMP L2140
.L21BA
    LDX #&04
.L21BC
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA zp_scroll_col
    CMP #&F0
    BEQ L21EB
    LDA hazard_x,X
    ADC hazard_step,X
    LDY hazard_y,X
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&01
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
.L21EB
    JSR missile_collide_hazard
    JMP L2140
.L21F1
    LDA #&00
    STA hazard_x,X
    LDY hazard_y,X
    TAX
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX data_16F5
    DEC hazard_step,X
    LDY hazard_step,X
    BEQ L2237
    LDA #&FF
    CLC
.L220B
    INY
    ADC #&20
    CPY #&04
    BNE L220B
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA hazard_type,X
    TAX
    LDA lev_hazard_ptr_hi,X
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA lev_hazard_ptr_lo,X
    ADC sprite_src_lo
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_flip,X
    STA zp_sprite_dir_flag
    LDA hazard_step,X
    TAX
    JMP L21BC
.L2237
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&01
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA #&00
    STA hazard_type,X
    JMP L2140

.update_hazard_slot
    JSR hazard_type_dispatch  \ Per-frame action for one hazard slot (X = slot index). Two steps: (1) call hazard_type_dispatch for the per-type immediate action; if the dispatch path bumped hazard_type past &14 (the death-anim range), jump to hazard_death_step. (2) Otherwise gate frame-advance on zp_7F == 4 (the animation phase tick — zp_7F cycles 3/4 across frames, so anim only advances 50% of the time) and fall into hazard_anim_advance.
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&14
    BCC L2260
    JMP hazard_death_step
.L2260
    LDA zp_7F
    CMP #&04
    BEQ hazard_anim_advance
    RTS

.hazard_anim_advance
    \ Animation-frame state machine for one hazard slot — keyed on hazard_type[X]:
    \ type < &04 → anim_loop_1_to_3 (3-frame anim loop: 1→2→3→1, with type 4 hit briefly to spawn a bullet then immediately wrapped back to 1)
    \ type &08 or &09 → anim_toggle_8_9 (EOR #1 — flame-firing hazard alternates between pre-fire pose &08 and post-fire idle &09)
    \ type &0F → anim_set_type_10 (2-frame loop with &10)
    \ type &10 → anim_set_type_F (2-frame loop with &0F)
    \ &04..&07, &0A..&0E, &11..&13 → hazard_anim_done (no animation — these are either action types that mutate to their own next state on dispatch, or static decor)
    \ type ≥ &14 → hazard_death_step (the explosion-animation tail).
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&04
    BCC anim_loop_1_to_3
    CMP #&08
    BEQ anim_toggle_8_9
    CMP #&09
    BEQ anim_toggle_8_9
    CMP #&0F
    BEQ anim_set_type_10
    CMP #&10
    BEQ anim_set_type_F
    CMP #&14
    BCC hazard_anim_done
    JMP hazard_death_step

.anim_loop_1_to_3
    INC hazard_type,X  \ Small-hazard 3-frame animation loop (types 1, 2, 3). INC type; on hitting type 4 (which is the 'fire' marker, NOT a frame), wrap back to type 1. Note: type 4 IS reached momentarily — hazard_type_dispatch runs FIRST and enqueues a bullet on type 4, then this routine wraps the type back to 1.
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&04
    BNE hazard_anim_done
    LDA #&01
    STA hazard_type,X
    RTS

.anim_toggle_8_9
    EOR #&01  \ Flame-firing hazard 2-state toggle. EOR #&01 flips between type &08 (about-to-fire pose; on the next dispatch call this triggers spawn_flame which itself bumps the slot to &09) and type &09 (post-fire idle).
    STA hazard_type,X
    RTS

.hazard_anim_done
    RTS  \ Shared 'no animation' RTS — branches here from hazard_anim_advance for hazard types that don't auto-advance their frame (force-fields, enemies already-advanced by dispatch, idle states).

.hazard_death_step
    INC hazard_type,X  \ Explosion-animation step for a dying hazard. INC hazard_type so it walks &14 → &15 → ... → &1B (= 8 frames using lev_hazard_ptr_*[20..27]); on reaching &1C clears the slot completely (hazard_type/_x/_y = 0). Triggered when a hazard's HP hits 0 (check_bullet_hits sets hazard_type = &14 to start the death anim).
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&1C
    BNE hazard_anim_done
    LDA #&00
    STA hazard_type,X
    STA hazard_x,X
    STA hazard_y,X
    RTS

.hazard_type_dispatch
    \ Hazard per-type IMMEDIATE action — called once per frame per active slot from update_hazard_slot, before frame-advance. Dispatch table by hazard_type[X]:
    \ type &04 → enqueue_hazard_bullet (hazard fires a leftward 4×2-px white bullet; pool at hazard_bullet_x/_y, 7 slots)
    \ type &06 → spawn_hazard_missile (CODE2: launch a vertical 4×6-px yellow-red rocket that horizontally homes on the player; pool at hazard_missile_x/_y, 2 slots)
    \ type &07 → forcefield_render (this slot IS a force-field — re-noise the strip every frame)
    \ type &08 → spawn_flame (start the one-shot 32×8-px flame projectile; auto-mutates to type 9 on success)
    \ type &13 → enqueue_hazard_bullet (same as type 4 — second hazard variant that fires a bullet)
    \ else     → RTS (no per-frame action; the slot just gets drawn and frame-advanced).
    LDA hazard_type,X
    CMP #&04
    BNE L22BC
    JMP enqueue_hazard_bullet
.L22BC
    CMP #&13
    BNE L22CF
    JMP enqueue_hazard_bullet

.anim_set_type_10
    LDA #&10  \ Frame-advance for type-&0F hazards → set hazard_type = &10. Pairs with anim_set_type_F to form a 2-frame ping-pong (F↔10) for whichever hazard type this is (likely a 2-frame animated decor / persistent enemy with no death state).
    STA hazard_type,X
    RTS

.anim_set_type_F
    LDA #&0F  \ Frame-advance for type-&10 hazards → set hazard_type = &0F. The other half of the F↔10 ping-pong (see anim_set_type_10).
    STA hazard_type,X
    RTS
.L22CF
    CMP #&06
    BNE L22D6
    JMP spawn_hazard_missile
.L22D6
    CMP #&07
    BNE L22DD
    JMP forcefield_render
.L22DD
    CMP #&08
    BNE L22E4
    JMP spawn_flame
.L22E4
    RTS

.enqueue_hazard_bullet
    LDA zp_get_ready_erase  \ Enqueue a hazard bullet — called from hazard_type_dispatch for hazard types &04 and &13. Scans hazard_bullet_x[6..1] for a &FF (free) slot; on found, stores `hazard_x[firer] - 1` at hazard_bullet_x[slot] and `hazard_y[firer] - &10` at hazard_bullet_y[slot] (Y lifted by 16 px to fire from above the hazard). Plays sfx_fire. If the firer is already at hazard_x < &08 (almost off-screen left) the bullet is suppressed — there's not enough screen left for it to fly. Per-frame mover: update_hazard_bullets. The bullet sprite is a 4×2-px white block at `hazard_bullet_sprite` (= &7E00, two bytes &77 poked by Loader2 line 1060). The per-frame mover plots a 3×2 sprite from `hazard_bullet_sprite` (= the visible white col 0 + two zero erase-trail cols 1..2 that blank the bullet's previous position since hazards bullets move LEFT 2 px/frame). The deactivation erase is a 2×2 stamp from `lev_erase_brush + &102` (4 zero bytes).
    CMP #&02
    BEQ L22EC
    RTS
.L22EC
    LDX #n_hazard_bullets
.L22EE
    LDA hazard_bullet_x,X
    CMP #&FF
    BEQ L22FC
    DEX
    BNE L22EE
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS
.L22FC
    STX data_16F6
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP #&08
    BCS L230D
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS
.L230D
    LDX data_16F6
    STA hazard_bullet_x,X
    DEC hazard_bullet_x,X
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_y,X
    LDX data_16F6
    SEC
    SBC #&10
    STA hazard_bullet_y,X
    JSR sfx_fire
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

.forcefield_render
    LDA forcefield_active
    CMP #&01
    BNE L2334
    RTS
.L2334
    LDA #&01
    STA forcefield_active
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_y,X
    LDY hazard_flip,X
    BNE L234A
    SEC
    SBC #&20
    JMP forcefield_draw_or_erase
.L234A
    CLC
    ADC #&20

.forcefield_draw_or_erase
    STA forcefield_y
    LDA hazard_x,X
    STX data_16F8
    STA forcefield_x
    LDY forcefield_y
    TAX
    CPX #&02
    BCC forcefield_erase
    CPX #&25
    BCS forcefield_erase
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    JSR lfsr_random
    LDA rndval256
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #&80
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA zp_player_x
    CMP forcefield_x
    BCS L23A1
    ADC #&04
    CMP forcefield_x
    BCC L23A1
    LDA zp_player_y
    SBC #&0C
    STA zp_test_x
    LDA forcefield_y
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L23A1
    SBC #&20
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS L23A1
    JSR lose_a_life
.L23A1
    LDX data_16F8
    STX data_16F5
    RTS

.forcefield_erase
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #&00
    STA forcefield_active
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

\ ----- data &23C5..&23C8 -----
.forcefield_x
    \ Force-field current X — last column it was drawn at; used by L210A to erase before forcefield_render redraws a fresh strip.
    EQUB &FF
.forcefield_y
    \ Force-field current Y — paired with forcefield_x.
    EQUB &FF
.forcefield_active
    \ Force-field active flag: 1 = a force-field was drawn last frame and needs erasing this frame, 0 = clean. Set by forcefield_draw_or_erase, cleared by L210A's early erase branch (and by forcefield_erase if the field went off-screen).
    EQUB &00

\ ----- code &23C8..&2554 -----
.missile_collide_hazard
    LDY player_missile_x  \ Per-frame test of both player missiles against the current hazard slot (X = hazard slot index, passed in via data_16F5). Sets up zp_test_x = upper_x + 3 and zp_test_y = upper_y - 4, calls `missile_hazard_box_test` with Y = 0 if the upper slot is active; then repeats with the lower slot's Y (zp_test_y = lower_y - 4) and Y = 1. Called from update_hazards' per-slot tail (L21AC, L21EB).
    INY
    INY
    INY
    STY zp_test_x
    LDA player_missile_y
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA player_missile_active
    CMP #&01
    BNE L23E4
    LDY #&00
    JSR missile_hazard_box_test
.L23E4
    LDA player_missile_y + 1
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA player_missile_active + 1
    CMP #&01
    BNE L23F8
    LDY #&01
    JSR missile_hazard_box_test
.L23F8
    RTS

.missile_hazard_box_test
    LDX data_16F5  \ Box-test the hazard at slot X (data_16F5) against the test point (zp_test_x, zp_test_y). Hit window: hazard_x in [test_x - 5, test_x] AND hazard_y in [test_y, test_y + &20]. On hit → `missile_hit_hazard`. Y on entry encodes which missile is being tested (0 = upper, 1 = lower) and is used by the hit path to deactivate the right slot and pick the right Y coordinate.
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L2404
    RTS
.L2404
    ADC #&05
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS L240B
    RTS
.L240B
    LDA hazard_y,X
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCS L2413
    RTS
.L2413
    SBC #&20
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC missile_hit_hazard
    RTS

.missile_hit_hazard
    JSR sfx_explode  \ Player missile hits hazard. Plays sfx_explode; uses the Y passed in (0 = upper, 1 = lower) to deactivate the corresponding `player_missile_active[Y]` and erase the corresponding sprite at (player_missile_x[Y], player_missile_y[Y]). Then DECs hazard_hp[X] by 4 — on kill (hp == 0) jumps to L2458 (the hazard-death path); on damage-but-not-killed RTSes.
    TYA
    TAX
    LDA #&00
    STA player_missile_active,X
    LDY player_missile_y,X
    LDX player_missile_x
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #&01
    STA zp_sprite_dir_flag
    LDX #&05
    LDY #&08
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_hp,X
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA hazard_hp,X
    BEQ L2458
    CMP #&08
    BCS L2458
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS
.L2458
    LDA #&14
    LDX data_16F5
    STA hazard_type,X
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

.spawn_flame
    LDA flame_state  \ Spawn the flame projectile. Called from hazard_type_dispatch when a hazard of type 8 wants to fire. Refuses if `flame_state != 0` (only one flame at a time) or if the firing hazard's `hazard_x < &0C` (it has already scrolled too far left to spawn from). On success: mutates the firing hazard to type 9 (the post-fire idle state), copies its position into `flame_x` / `flame_y` (with a per-flip Y offset), and sets `flame_state = 1` to start the 6-frame animation.
    BEQ L246A
    RTS
.L246A
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP #&0C
    BCS L2472
    RTS
.L2472
    LDA #&09
    STA hazard_type,X
    LDA hazard_y,X
    LDY hazard_flip,X
    SEC
    CPY #&01
    BNE L2487
    SBC #&08
    JMP L2489
.L2487
    SBC #&10
.L2489
    STA flame_y
    LDA hazard_x,X
    SBC #&09
    STA flame_x
    LDA #&01
    STA flame_state
    RTS

.flame_x
    NOP  \ Flame projectile X coord — column. DEC'd by 1 per call to update_flame so the flame drifts left through the playfield as the scenery scrolls. When it falls below &02 the flame deactivates (off-screen left).

.flame_y
    NOP  \ Flame projectile Y coord (in scanlines).

.flame_state
    BRK  \ Flame state machine: 0 = inactive (slot free for a new spawn); 1..6 = animation frames (1=&3B00, 2=&3B40, 3=&3B80, then ping-pongs back 4=&3B80, 5=&3B40, 6=&3B00); 7 = deactivate next call. Each call to update_flame INCs the state (via advance_flame_state) or jumps straight to 7 if the player has been hit.

.update_flame
    LDX flame_x  \ Per-frame flame update (called from update_hazards when `flame_state != 0`). Erases the previous 32×8 frame, shifts the flame left by 1 px (DEC flame_x), then either re-plots the next animation frame from `gfx_flame_frame0..2` (states 1..6) or deactivates (state 7 / off-screen). Each frame is 8 byte-cols × 8 lines = 32×8 px. There is only ever one flame on screen — `spawn_flame` checks `flame_state` and refuses to start a new one until this slot is free.
    LDY flame_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&08
    LDY #&08
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    DEC flame_x
    LDA flame_x
    CMP #&02
    BCS plot_flame
    JMP deactivate_flame

.plot_flame
    TAX  \ Plot the flame at its updated position. Dispatches by `flame_state` to one of three frame plotters: state 1/6 → `plot_flame_frame_0` (`gfx_flame_frame0` at &3B00), state 2/5 → `plot_flame_frame_1` (`gfx_flame_frame1` at &3B40), state 3/4 → `plot_flame_frame_2` (`gfx_flame_frame2` at &3B80). State 7 → `deactivate_flame`.
    LDY flame_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&08
    LDY #&08
    LDA #HI(gfx_flame_frame0)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA flame_state
    CMP #&01
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_0
    CMP #&02
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_1
    CMP #&03
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_2
    CMP #&04
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_2
    CMP #&05
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_1
    CMP #&06
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_0
    CMP #&07
    BEQ deactivate_flame
    BNE plot_flame_frame_0
    RTS

.plot_flame_frame_0
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame0)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.plot_flame_frame_1
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame1)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.plot_flame_frame_2
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame2)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.deactivate_flame
    LDA #&00  \ Deactivate the flame — `flame_state = 0`. Reached when the flame has reached its final animation frame, drifts off the left edge, or has hit the player.
    STA flame_state
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

.flame_collide_player
    LDA flame_x  \ Box-test the flame against the player. Collision box is offset (+4, -4) from the plotted position, 6 px wide × &18 (24) lines tall. On hit: set `flame_state = 7` (so the next call deactivates) and JMP `lose_a_life`.
    CLC
    ADC #&04
    STA zp_test_x
    LDA flame_y
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA zp_player_x
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS advance_flame_state
    ADC #&06
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC advance_flame_state
    LDA zp_player_y
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC advance_flame_state
    SBC #&18
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCS advance_flame_state
    LDA #&07
    STA flame_state
    JMP lose_a_life

.advance_flame_state
    INC flame_state  \ Tail of `flame_collide_player` for the no-hit case — INC `flame_state` so the next frame plots the next animation step (1→2→3→4→5→6→7→deactivate).
    RTS

\ ----- data &2554..&2555 -----
.fire_cooldown_reload
    EQUB &06

\ ----- code &2555..&25A1 -----
.pod_collide_enemy
    LDA pod_attached  \ Per-frame pod ↔ enemy collision check (X = enemy slot). Only runs when the force-pod power-up is attached to the player (`pod_attached == 1`) and the enemy slot is active (`enemy_state < 9`). Test box is 3×&14 px at (player_x+8, player_y-11) — matches where draw_player_pod plots the pod sprite (offset (+5, +1) from the player). On hit: marks the slot &0A (expired), plays OSWRCH &07 (collision bell), runs `add_score_x1` for the score, and INCs `pickup_kill_count` (the kill-milestone counter that triggers a pickup spawn every 10 hits). Differs from `check_player_collisions` in that this is the POD doing damage to the enemy (scoring), whereas check_player_collisions is the enemy damaging the player (lose_a_life). Called from update_enemies per-slot.
    CMP #&01
    BEQ L255D
    RTS
.L255D
    LDA enemy_state,X
    CMP #&09
    BCC L2565
    RTS
.L2565
    LDA zp_player_x
    CLC
    ADC #&08
    STA zp_test_x
    LDA zp_player_y
    SEC
    SBC #&0B
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA enemy_x,X
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS L259E
    ADC #&03
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC L259E
    LDA enemy_y,X
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC L259E
    SEC
    SBC #&14
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCS L259E
    LDA #&0A
    STA enemy_state,X
    LDA #&07
    JSR OSWRCH
    JSR add_score_x1
    INC pickup_kill_count
.L259E
    RTS

.pickup_count
    BRK

.pickup_kill_count
    BRK

\ ----- data &25A1..&25AA -----
.pickup_tier_flag
    \ 8-element pickup tier-flag array (&25A1..&25A8), indexed by `pickup_count - 1`. Set by `set_pickup_tier_flag` to mark each tier as reached. Three slots overlap with named flags whose meaning is consumed elsewhere: tier 3 (offset +2) = `pod_attached` (pod sprite + pod_collide_enemy kicks in), tier 5 (offset +4) = `force_pod_state` (pod_fire enabled + force_pod_anim runs), tier 7 (offset +6) = `player_missiles_unlocked` (`fire_player_missiles` enabled — a paired upper+lower 5×8 missile pattern fires on the next fire-button press; the spawn-block side-effect just falls out — there's nothing left to upgrade). Tiers 2, 4, 6, 8 (offsets +1, +3, +5, +7) ARE written but nothing reads them — orphan flags, presumably scaffolding for power-ups that were planned but never implemented (no consumer code).
    EQUB &EA, &EA
.pod_attached
    EQUB &EA, &EA
.force_pod_state
    EQUB &EA, &EA
.player_missiles_unlocked
    EQUB &EA, &EA
.data_25A9
    EQUB &EA

\ ----- code &25AA..&268F -----
.try_spawn_pickup
    LDA pickup_kill_count  \ Try to start a power-up pickup. Triggered when pickup_kill_count (the kill-milestone counter — INC'd in check_bullet_hits at enemy-hit values 3/5/7) reaches &0A. Requires no pickup already active (pickup_state == 0) and `player_missiles_unlocked != 1` (= the 7th-pickup ceiling — once the player has collected 7 power-ups, no more spawn). On success: stash player_y in pickup_y, set pickup_x = &27 (right edge col 39), pickup_state = 1 (animation start), play sfx_level_start.
    CMP #&0A
    BCS L25B2
    RTS
.L25B2
    LDA #&00
    STA pickup_kill_count
    LDA pickup_state
    BEQ L25BD
    RTS
.L25BD
    LDA player_missiles_unlocked
    CMP #&01
    BNE L25C5
    RTS
.L25C5
    LDA zp_player_y
    STA pickup_y
    LDA #&27
    STA pickup_x
    LDA #&01
    STA pickup_state
    JMP sfx_level_start

.add_score_x1
    CLC  \ Score accumulator: ADD `zp_score_acc` to the units digit (`score + 4`) and propagate the carry chain through the 4 display digits (score+3 → +2 → +1 → +0). The score buffer is 6 bytes MSD-first at `score..score + 5`: bytes 0..3 are the four visible display digits, byte 4 is the actual units (which is what gets incremented), byte 5 is always 0 (the trailing '0' shown on screen so a score of 1230 stores as {0,1,2,3,0,0} and a +10 award stores `zp_score_acc = 1` then calls `add_score_x10`). Carries cascade through `add_score_carry_x{1,10,100,1000}`.
    LDA score + 4
    ADC zp_score_acc
    STA score + 4
    CMP #&0A
    BCS add_score_carry_x1
    RTS

.add_score_x10
    CLC  \ Score accumulator x10: ADD `zp_score_acc` to the tens digit (`score + 3`) and carry-chain through score+2 → +1 → +0. Equivalent to `add_score_x1` with the accumulator pre-multiplied by 10. The fall-through code at &25EE..&2618 (extra ADC blocks for score+2/+1/+0) is unreachable — RTS after each carry check exits before the next block, and the routine instead jumps straight into the shared `add_score_carry_*` chain via the BCS branches.
    LDA score + 3
    ADC zp_score_acc
    STA score + 3
    CMP #&0A
    BCS add_score_carry_x10
    RTS
    CLC
    LDA score + 2
    ADC zp_score_acc
    STA score + 2
    CMP #&0A
    BCS add_score_carry_x100
    RTS
    CLC
    LDA score + 1
    ADC zp_score_acc
    STA score + 1
    CMP #&0A
    BCS add_score_carry_x1000
    RTS
    CLC
    LDA score
    ADC zp_score_acc
    STA score
    RTS

.add_score_carry_x1
    SEC  \ Score carry (units → tens): subtract 10 from the overflowed units digit, INC the tens digit (score+3), and if THAT now equals 10 fall into `add_score_carry_x10` to propagate. Reached from `add_score_x1` when score+4 wraps past 10.
    SBC #&0A
    STA score + 4
    INC score + 3
    LDA score + 3
    CMP #&0A
    BEQ add_score_carry_x10
    RTS

.add_score_carry_x10
    SEC  \ Score carry (tens → hundreds): subtract 10 from score+3, INC score+2 (hundreds), recurse if it also wraps. Shared by `add_score_x1` and `add_score_x10`.
    SBC #&0A
    STA score + 3
    INC score + 2
    LDA score + 2
    CMP #&0A
    BEQ add_score_carry_x100
    RTS

.add_score_carry_x100
    SEC  \ Score carry (hundreds → thousands): subtract 10 from score+2, INC score+1 (thousands), recurse if it also wraps.
    SBC #&0A
    STA score + 2
    INC score + 1
    LDA score + 1
    CMP #&0A
    BEQ add_score_carry_x1000
    RTS

.add_score_carry_x1000
    SEC  \ Score carry (thousands → ten-thousands): subtract 10 from score+1, INC score (the MSD = ten-thousands). No further carry — overflow past 99,999,0 silently wraps.
    SBC #&0A
    STA score + 1
    INC score
    RTS

.starfield_init
    LDY #&00
    LDX #&00
.L265A
    LDA starfield_pos_lo,X
    STA zp_screen_ptr_lo
    LDA starfield_pos_hi,X
    STA zp_screen_ptr_hi
    LDA starfield_type,X
    CMP #&03
    BNE L2670
    LDA #&02
    JMP L2672
.L2670
    LDA #&20
.L2672
    STA (zp_screen_ptr_lo),Y
    INX
    CPX #&3C
    BNE L265A
    LDX #&00
.L267B
    LDA hazard_type,X
    BNE L268A
    INX
    CPX #&08
    BNE L267B
    LDA #&01
    STA stage_clear_flag
.L268A
    LDA #&01
    STA zp_sprite_dir_flag
    RTS

\ ----- data &268F..&2693 -----
.stage_clear_flag
    EQUB &EA
.pickup_x
    \ Power-up pickup X coordinate (column). DEC'd by 1 each subframe of game_step (so the pickup drifts leftward 16 px/sec = 4 px per game_step). When it hits 0, update_pickup deactivates and erases. Initial value &27 (right edge) on spawn from try_spawn_pickup.
    EQUB &EA
.pickup_y
    \ Power-up pickup Y coordinate (scanline) — captured from player_y at the moment try_spawn_pickup ran, then held constant for the lifetime of the pickup.
    EQUB &EA
.pickup_state
    \ Power-up pickup state: 0 = inactive (slot free for a new spawn). Non-zero = active, with the value selecting the sprite frame for the flashing animation (2/6 → gfx_pickup_yellow, 3/5 → gfx_pickup_red, others → erase) — wraps at &0A back to 1.
    EQUB &EA

\ ----- code &2693..&27E7 -----
.update_pickup
    LDA pickup_state  \ Per-subframe power-up pickup updater. Returns immediately if pickup_state == 0. Otherwise calls L275F (collision test?), conditionally advances state, DECs pickup_x (drifts the pickup leftward 1 px per subframe), and on pickup_x == 0 deactivates and erases. While alive, plots one of two sprites (`gfx_pickup_yellow` or `gfx_pickup_red`) keyed on the current pickup_state value (state 2/6 = yellow, 3/5 = red, 4 = ?, others = erase) — gives the pickup a flashing animation as it crosses the playfield.
    BNE L2699
    RTS
.L2699
    JSR pickup_collected
    LDA pickup_state
    BNE L26A2
    RTS
.L26A2
    LDA zp_7F
    CMP #&04
    BNE L26AB
    INC pickup_state
.L26AB
    DEC pickup_x
    LDA pickup_x
    BNE L26CF
    STA pickup_state
    LDX #&00
    LDY pickup_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&03
    LDY #&10
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L26CF
    LDX pickup_x
    LDY pickup_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&03
    LDY #&10
    LDA pickup_state
    CMP #&01
    BEQ L2737
    CMP #&02
    BEQ L2703
    CMP #&03
    BEQ L2744
    CMP #&04
    BEQ L2751
    CMP #&05
    BEQ L2744
    CMP #&06
    BEQ L2703
    CMP #&0A
    BCC L2737
    LDA #&01
    STA pickup_state
    JMP L2737
.L2703
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_yellow)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_yellow)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_red)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_red)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_checker)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_checker)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #LO(gfx_text_pause)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_text_pause)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L2737
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_red)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_red)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L2744
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_checker)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_checker)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L2751
    LDA #LO(gfx_pickup_white)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_pickup_white)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L275E
    RTS

.pickup_collected
    LDX zp_player_x  \ Per-subframe pickup ↔ player collision test + tier ladder. Box-test the player against (pickup_x, pickup_y) with a (6 × &1C) hit window; miss → RTS. On hit: clear pickup_state, erase the pickup sprite (3×&10 brush), play sfx_level_start, add 100 to score (add_score_x10 with zp_score_acc=10? — TODO confirm), INC pickup_count, plot the +1 icon on the status row, then dispatch to `apply_pickup_tier`. Effects ladder (cumulative per game/life): #1 → fast fire (fire_cooldown_reload = 3); #2 → pickup_tier_flag+1 (unused); #3 → pod_attached = 1; #4 → unused; #5 → force_pod_state = 1 AND reset fire timer zp_8A = 8; #6 → unused; #7 → player_missiles_unlocked = 1; #8+ → no effect (count clamped). Called from update_pickup every active subframe.
    DEX
    TXA
    CMP pickup_x
    BCS L275E
    ADC #&06
    CMP pickup_x
    BCC L275E
    LDA zp_player_y
    CLC
    ADC #&04
    CMP pickup_y
    BCC L275E
    SBC #&1C
    CMP pickup_y
    BCS L275E
    LDA #&00
    STA pickup_state
    LDX pickup_x
    LDY pickup_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&03
    LDY #&10
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JSR sfx_level_start
    JSR add_score_x10
    LDX #&08
    LDY #&57
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(gfx_icon_01)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(gfx_icon_01)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    INC pickup_count
    LDX pickup_count
    CPX #&08
    BCS L27C5
    LDY #&08
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
.L27C5
    LDA pickup_count
    CMP #&01
    BNE apply_pickup_tier
    LDA #&03
    STA fire_cooldown_reload
    RTS

.apply_pickup_tier
    TAX  \ Tier-flag dispatcher. X = pickup_count, decrement to get the tier index (0-based), then jump to `set_pickup_tier_flag` if X < 7. Falls through to RTS for tier indices >= 7 (i.e. pickup_count >= 8).
    DEX
    CPX #&07
    BCC set_pickup_tier_flag
    RTS

.set_pickup_tier_flag
    LDA #&01  \ Set the per-tier pickup flag at `pickup_tier_flag,X`. The interesting tiers are X=2 (= pod_attached), X=4 (= force_pod_state, also resets zp_8A), X=6 (= player_missiles_unlocked). Tiers X=1/3/5/7 write to dead slots.
    STA pickup_tier_flag,X
    CPX #&04
    BNE L27E6
    LDA #&08
    STA zp_8A
.L27E6
    RTS
